                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Expectation:</strong> Food cost will naturally improve as sales increase. At $78K/month with better purchasing and less waste, targeting 30-31% is realistic. This analysis uses 33.2% conservatively for current scenarios, with 30% shown as achievable target in growth scenarios.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <div class="section-title">What Sales Level Justifies Current Staffing?</div>
                
                <div class="methodology-box">
                    <strong>Calculation Method:</strong> Current monthly labor cost Ã· Target labor % = Required sales to justify staffing
                </div>
                
                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Target Labor %</th>
