            <div class="section">
                <div class="section-title">Scenario Breakdowns</div>
                
                <div class="methodology-box">
                    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--accent);">SCENARIO 1: SURVIVAL MODE - 10 Staff</h3>
                    <strong>Monthly Labor:</strong> $27,133 (43% of sales)<br>
                    <strong>Weekly Hours:</strong> 291 hours<br>
                    <strong>Financial Impact:</strong> Still losing -$7,959/month (but saves $25,182 vs current)<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>WHO STAYS (Definite KEEP):</strong><br>
                    â€¢ Core Team: Andrew Stewart (GM), Oscar Sparbel, Mikey Williams<br>
                    â€¢ Security: Andrew Wright<br>
                    â€¢ Top Cooks: David Jones, Dylan Brookshire<br>
                    â€¢ Top FOH: Aaron Warnock, Kyran Lindsay<br>
                    â€¢ Prep: Samuel Gander (cross-trains to line)<br>
                    â€¢ +1 flexible position based on schedule gaps<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>WHO GOES (8-9 people cut):</strong><br>
                    All additional leads (Milo, Alivia, Lawrence), low-hour cooks (Vince, Michael), low-hour FOH (Ava, Eliza, Josh, Alex), redundant prep (David F.)<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>RISKS:</strong> Extreme burnout, no backup coverage, quality may suffer, very difficult to execute growth
                </div>
                
                <div class="methodology-box" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--warning);">SCENARIO 2: RIGHT-SIZED - 13 Staff</h3>
                    <strong>Monthly Labor:</strong> $30,288 (48% of sales)<br>
                    <strong>Weekly Hours:</strong> 325 hours<br>
                    <strong>Financial Impact:</strong> Still losing -$11,114/month (but saves $22,055 vs current)<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>WHO STAYS (Definite KEEP + Additions):</strong><br>
                    â€¢ Core Team: Andrew Stewart (GM), Oscar Sparbel, Mikey Williams<br>
                    â€¢ Security: Andrew Wright<br>
                    â€¢ Additional Lead: Milo Blue (for coverage and backup management)<br>
                    â€¢ Cooks: David Jones, Dylan Brookshire + 1 cross-trained from leads<br>
                    â€¢ FOH: Aaron Warnock, Kyran Lindsay + 2 more from MAYBE group<br>
                    â€¢ Prep: Samuel Gander<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>WHO GOES (5-7 people cut):</strong><br>
                    Definitely: Vince, Michael, Josh, Alex, David F.<br>
                    Possibly: 1-2 from Alivia, Lawrence, Ava, Eliza depending on final schedule<br><br>
                    
                    <strong>ASSESSMENT:</strong> Proper staffing for $63K/month operation, sustainable operations, better service quality, still need sales growth for profitability
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <div class="section-title">Decision-Making Criteria</div>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Priority 1: Core Team + Security = Absolute Non-Negotiable</strong><br>
                    Andrew (GM), Oscar, Mikey, and Andrew Wright must be retained in ANY scenario. They represent the operational foundation and leadership of the restaurant.
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Priority 2: Cross-Training Ability = Major Competitive Advantage</strong><br>
                    Employees who can work multiple positions (cook/line, FOH/expo, prep/cook) provide schedule flexibility and reduce need for specialists. Samuel (prep who can work line) and Oscar/Mikey (can do everything) exemplify this value.
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Priority 3: Hours Worked = Commitment Indicator</strong><br>
                    Weekly hours strongly correlate with reliability and availability. David Jones (41.5 hrs), Oscar (40.6), Aaron Warnock (35.5), Dylan (34.1), and Samuel (33.7) show consistent high commitment. Low-hour employees (Michael 2.8 hrs, Alex 6.1 hrs) indicate limited availability or commitment.
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Priority 4: Late-Night Availability = Premium Value</strong><br>
                    Friday/Saturday midnight-4am shifts generate 25%+ of revenue but are hardest to staff. Employees willing and able to work these shifts have outsized value to operations.
                </div>
                
                <div class="key-insight">
                    <strong>Priority 5: Speed, Quality, Reliability Balanced with Cost</strong><br>
                    A $21/hr reliable employee who shows up on time and works efficiently is more valuable than a $17/hr employee with attendance issues. However, wage premiums should align with actual performance differential.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
