                <div class="methodology-box">
                    <strong>Data Collection Period:</strong> November 24-30, 2025 (one-week payroll snapshot)<br>
                    <strong>Analysis Date:</strong> December 3, 2025<br>
                    <strong>Methodology:</strong> Actual payroll data analyzed, projected to monthly figures using 4.33-week multiplier
                </div>
                
                <h3 style="margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;">Primary Data Sources</h3>
                
                <div class="assumption-item">
                    <div class="assumption-label">1. Sales Data</div>
                    <strong>Source:</strong> Toast POS Sales Summary (60-day lookback)<br>
                    <strong>Total Monthly Sales:</strong> $63,099.21<br>
                    <strong>Weekly Average:</strong> $14,570<br>
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Late-night hours (12am-4am Fri/Sat) represent 25%+ of weekly revenue
                </div>
                
                <div class="assumption-item">
                    <div class="assumption-label">2. Labor Data</div>
                    <strong>Source:</strong> Gusto payroll export (Nov 24-30, 2025)<br>
                    <strong>Weekly Hours:</strong> 548.46 hours<br>
                    <strong>Weekly Wages:</strong> $8,553.48<br>
                    <strong>Average Hourly Rate:</strong> $15.60<br>
                    <strong>Loaded Rate (w/ employer taxes):</strong> $20.27<br>
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Includes 30% markup for employer-side payroll taxes, workers comp, benefits
                </div>
                
                <div class="assumption-item">
                    <div class="assumption-label">3. Food Cost Data (ACTUAL)</div>
                    <strong>Source:</strong> November 2025 vendor invoices<br>
                    <strong>Total November COGS:</strong> $20,977.30<br>
                    <strong>Food Cost %:</strong> 33.2% of sales<br>
                    <strong>Vendors:</strong> US Foods, Earthly Gourmet, Cash & Carry, Catscratch Cookies, Flatiron Pepper, Portland Soda<br>
                    <strong>Note:</strong> This is 3.2 percentage points above industry standard (30%), representing $2,047/month in excess food costs
                </div>
                
